result.execSummary:
The defendant Dustin L Davis was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
Court orders defendant to pay all cost, fees and surcharges, including DNA surcharge by 11/15/2016 or a civil judgment to be entered with tax intercept.  Bail on deposit to be applied if applicable.
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
Consecutive to: CONSECUTIVE to any sentence with credit for 10 days served; Straight time, with release to the Day Reporting Center. Court recommends against electronic monitoring.

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor. Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.
Court does not suspend driving privileges.

Defendant Dustin L Davis in court with attorney Jason Daniel Baltz.  Defendant Dustin L Davis in custody.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Deputy court clerk: LMS.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made as to sentencing.
Court sentenced defendant to serve 7 MONTHS in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to any sentence with credit for 10 days served; Straight time, with release to the Day Reporting Center. Court recommends against electronic monitoring. 

Court orders defendant to pay all cost, fees and surcharges, including DNA surcharge by 11/15/2016 or a civil judgment to be entered with tax intercept.  Bail on deposit to be applied if applicable.

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.  Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor. Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored. Court advised defendant of his right to seek postconviction relief.

Court does not suspend driving privileges.

Court denies defense request for expungment.

Defendant Dustin L Davis in court with attorney Jason Daniel Baltz.  Paul M. Hauer appeared for the State of Wisconsin (for ADA Chojnacki).    Filed, signed Deferred Prosecution Agreement.  The court reviewed the Agreement with the defendant.

The Court found the defendant guilty but WITHHELD entry.
The court approved the Deferred Prosecution Agreement and found it to be in the best interest of the parties and the general public.
